<TITLE> Ship breaking blast: 2 more bodies found </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 26 (bdnews24.com)  Another two bodies were found following a blast at a scrap ship in Sitakunda on Saturday, bringing the death toll to four, police said. Initially, two people were reported killed and at least 10 others injured after a gas cylinder exploded at the ship breaking site. Sitakunda police chief Monirul Islam said the blast occurred while workers were engaged in dismantling the ship of Rahim Steel and Ship Breaking Yard at around 10:30am. One body was identified in the aftermath as Selim Hossain. The most seriously injured workers were taken to Chittagong Medical College Hospital, others injured were admitted to Sitakunda upazila health complex, Islam said. Ship breaking is a growing industry in Bangladesh, with the thousands of tonnes of scrap metal being used by re-rolling mills, but concerns prevail over work safety . bdnews
